channel.title: Life
channel.description:
Is life more than the sum of it's parts? What if, it is, in fact less.
What if, not only are as lives as meaningless as what they appear to be on the surface, but they are in fact, more meaningless. What if what we do doesn't really matter in the long run, or even day to day. What if, tommorow, you woke up in a different life and forgot this one. If it happened every day would you ever notice?
So how bout it. It's not that lifes meaningless, it's that your life's meaningless. The human mind is a beautiful thing, but is your body really so special? Maybe what matters is not whether your alive or dead, but whether your mind is a beautiful place.

item.title: Life
item.dc:creator: @Aukake Aukake
item.description:
@Aukake wrote:

Something that is meaningful to me may or may not be meaningful to you. So, I'm saying I don't give two shits if my name shows up in a textbook somewhere. That stuff is not meaningful to me. What is meaningful is spending my time with people I enjoy that make me feel good about who I am and feeding my desire to sit in front of a computer for long periods of time and learn almost nothing. In that respect, my life is more meaningful than anyone elses'. 

If you go about life thinking it's meaningless, you're probably going to end up as one of those freaks that dress in all black and parents shun their children to the other side of the street so they don't have to pass you on the sidewalk.
